# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Git attributes
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Most of the repo can use the default text+autocrlf behaviour. The exceptions
# here are files where line-ending conversion would corrupt the content or
# break a hash check.

# RDS CA bundle — sha256 is pinned in every service Dockerfile; checking it
# out as CRLF on Windows or LF on Linux must produce IDENTICAL bytes. Treat
# as binary so git never touches the line endings, regardless of the user's
# core.autocrlf setting.
infrastructure/certs/rds-global-bundle.pem binary
